Valid inputs:

NEW <number of elements> 
    - Integers greater than and equal to 0
    - Edge case of 0

VIEW <list index | ALL>
    - Note that this can be an 'integer, which is a valid list index' or the literal 'ALL'

TYPE <list index>
REMOVE <list index>
    - Integer, which is a valid list index (greater than or equal to 0 is a quick first check)

INSERT <list index> <index> <value>
DELETE <list index> <index>
VIEW-NESTED <list index>


Invalid inputs:

Generally, if we have leading or trailing space UNLESS we are in the INSERT command -> then its ok
    - This means we should have special validation for the 3rd argument?


| NEW 5| INVALID COMMAND: INPUT - If the line DOES NOT start with a valid command
|NEW  5| INVALID COMMAND: NEW - If the line DOES start with a valid command, but the arguments or spacing is invalid
|NEW 5 | INVALID COMMAND: NEW
|NEW 5.1234| INVALID COMMAND: NEW
|NEW 5e| INVALID COMMAND: NEW
|NEW 5e-2| INVALID COMMAND: NEW
|NEW .5| INVALID COMMAND: NEW
|NEW A| INVALID COMMAND: NEW
|NEW | INVALID COMMAND: NEW
|NEW| INVALID COMMAND: NEW
|NEWa| INVALID COMMAND: INPUT
|b NEW| INVALID COMMAND: INPUT
|b| INVALID COMMAND: INPUT
|NE| INVALID COMMAND: INPUT
|NEW 0| - Valid but edge case

|VIEW 10| INVALID COMMAND: VIEW - 10 is not a valid list
|VIEW 9| INVALID COMMAND: VIEW - 9 was deleted
|VIEW -1| INVALID COMMAND: VIEW

|VIEW AL| INVALID COMMAND: VIEW
|VIEW ALL | INVALID COMMAND: VIEW
|VIEWALL| INVALID COMMAND: INPUT
|VIEW-ALL| INVALID COMMAND: INPUT
|VIEW ALL 1| INVALID COMMAND: VIEW
|VIEW  ALL| INVALID COMMAND: VIEW

|TYPE 10| INVALID COMMAND: TYPE - 10 is not a valid list
|TYPE 9| INVALID COMMAND: TYPE - 9 was deleted
|TYPE -1| INVALID COMMAND: TYPE

|REMOVE 10| INVALID COMMAND: REMOVE - 10 is not a valid list
|REMOVE 9| INVALID COMMAND: REMOVE - 9 was deleted
|REMOVE -1| INVALID COMMAND: REMOVE


|INSERT 10 0 x| INVALID COMMAND: INSERT - 10 is not a valid list
|INSERT 1 12 x| INVALID COMMAND: INSERT - 12 is outside the length of the list. We can have index <= length (i.e. 1 -> 2 -> 3 could be insert into the 3rd element)
|INSERT 1 3 x| - Valid edge
|INSERT 1 -12 x| INVALID COMMAND: INSERT
|INSERT 1 -4 x| - Valid edge for length = 3 (|idx| - 1 <= length)
|INSERT 1  12 x| INVALID COMMAND: INSERT
|INSERT  1 12 x| INVALID COMMAND: INSERT
|INSERT 1 12  x  | - Valid

|DELETE 1 3| INVALID COMMAND: DELETE (for length = 3)
|DELETE 1 -4| INVALID COMMAND: DELETE (|idx| <= length)
|DELETE 1 -3| - Valid edge 

|VIEW ALL NEW 1| INVALID COMMAND: VIEW
|NEW 1 INSERT 1 2 x| INVALID COMMAND: NEW
|NEW VIEW ALL| INVALID COMMAND: NEW
|\n| INVALID COMMAND: INPUT
| | INVALID COMMAND: INPUT


|NEW 0|
|VIEW 0| - should output nothing but a new line

|NEW 1|
|DELETE 1 0| - should output "List 0: " including the space

|NEW 1| - with no newline at the end?

|INSERT 1 0 hello world i am jognny| - this is valid


WHAT HAPPENDS WHEN WE STOP IN THE MIDDLE OF NEW COMMAND? - both buffers close :(



1st step: determine if the command is valid
    Find the first space. Copy from the begining up to the first space into command variable
    Check if the command variable matches defined commands
--- If its valid, continue. If its not, print "INVALID COMMAND: INPUT"; free(command) and return ---


2nd step: split arguments into arg && num_args
    split up to 3 times -> last argument may be able to be split more
        - if there are 3 args i.e. its an INSERT command, we will have to run the 3rd arg thru the same validation as anything in the NEW command
    populate args, num_args
    return

2.5th step: maintain a pointer to the head of the list of mtll
    We need this to be able to call functions, and validate we have valid <list index> and <index>.
    Create on startup with a null pointer?
    When we make the first list, we need to change it to point at the thing we just created.
    We also need to maintain an static? integer for the next list index
    We also need to, when removing the last list, change it back to a null pointer so we know the list is empty


3rd step: run some validation -> within the view() etc functions
    NEW needs a valid integer > 0
    VIEW needs "ALL"
    VIEW (if not "ALL"), TYPE, REMOVE, INSERT, DELETE, VIEW-NESTED all need a valid <list index> first
    INSERT, DELETE need a valid <index> second
    INSERT needs a valid <value> 3rd -> run thru NEW input validation

    function for valid <list index>, <index> and <value> (this should already be defined for NEW command)
    function specifically for NEW and VIEW "ALL" case

